headline: Fact check: Video predicting pandemic made in 2020, not 1956
Fact check: Oprah has no link to reports of abuse by Weinstein
details: A viral social media post falsely claims Oprah Winfrey helped Harvey Weinstein sexually abuse and harass women.

headline: Fact check: People experiencing homelessness can get stimulus
details: People who are experiencing homelessness can get the $1,400 stimulus if they file a 2020 tax return.

headline: Fact check: Photographer who filmed Capitol rioter not linked to CNN
details: A Facebook post falsely implicated CNN in the Jan. 6 riot at the U.S. Capitol.

headline: Fact check: Majority of immigrants in US illegally won't get stimulus checks
details: A viral Facebook post inaccurately claimed that immigrants who are not legally in the U.S. will receive $1,400 stimulus checks.

headline: Fact check: Will Rogers took a stand against government spending?
details: A viral 1932 quote from columnist Will Rogers is edited, and doesn't indicate Rogers was writing about a particular movement called technocracy.

headline: Fact check: Demand drives surge in diesel prices
details: Diesel and gas prices have steadily risen because increased movement and economic activity have increased demand. President Joe Biden isn't to blame.

headline: Fact check: El Chapo did not testify about Pelosi
details: Joaquín Guzmán did not testify at his U.S. trial, nor did his defense make any comment on House Speaker Nancy Pelosi. A claim stating that is false.

headline: Fact check: Hagler's death not related to COVID-19 vaccine
details: Various social media posts have linked boxing legend Marvin Hagler's death to the COVID-19 vaccine. They are false.

headline: Fact check: Image shows an illustration of sunset on Mars
details: A viral image shared on social media claiming to be the first image of a sunset on Mars is actually an illustration.

headline: Fact check: Mars Perseverance landing did happen
details: A recent meme posted to Facebook claims the Mars Perseverance mission did not happen because of the planet's atmospheric conditions. This is false.

headline: Fact check: Pelosi net worth isn't $196 million
details: A Facebook post that claims House Speaker Nancy Pelosi is worth $196 million is false. Using ranges from reports, it may be half that.

headline: Fact check: Story on circus tickets misattributed to Hepburn
details: A viral post claiming to be a short story from actress Katharine Hepburn was actually written by motivational speaker Dan Clark.

headline: Fact check: GOP governors have mixed record on mask mandates
details: A social media claim suggests 16 states do not have mask requirements because they are governed by Republicans. But that lacks context.

headline: Fact check: Pelosi staffer asked for altered SOTU video to be pulled
details: A claim that Drew Hammill demanded removal of videos of Nancy Pelosi ripping up then-President Donald Trump's State of the Union speech needs context.

headline: Fact check: Canadian nursing homes, orphanages remain separate
details: There is no evidence that orphanages and assisted-care living facilities were combined in Canada, as claimed in a viral Facebook post.

headline: Fact check: Claim of Coca-Cola bringing out worms from raw pork is a hoax
details: The claim that marinating a piece of raw pork in Coca-Cola will cause worms to crawl out is an urban legend.

headline: Fact check: Post falsely claims Pelosi was heard insulting Americans
details: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi did not call Americans "the dumbest people on earth." The claim originated on a satirical website.

headline: Fact check: No executive order, but Michigan does require masks
details: Michigan doesn't have an executive order requiring face masks, but it still has a statewide mask mandate.

headline: Fact check: Sneaker image won't reveal which side of brain is dominant
details: A 2017 image of a sneaker that recently resurfaced falsely claims to show which side of your brain is more dominant depending on the color you see.

headline: Fact check: CDC study links mask mandates to slowing COVID-19
details: A widely shared post from One America News Network claims that a CDC study found "masks have negligible impact on coronavirus numbers." This is false.

headline: Fact check: AOC, Gillibrand, Pelosi have spoken about Cuomo allegations
details: A post stating that five promient Democratic women haven't commented on allegations of sexual harassment against NY Gov. Andrew Cuomo is partly false.

headline: Fact check: Masks, vaccines counter COVID-19 spread
details: A Facebook post claims masks and vaccines have not worked against COVID-19. This is false.
